      <fact xml:id="fact-CO6polarIntegral">
          
      <p permid="QCd">
        The area of the ``fan-shaped'' region between the pole and <m>r=f(\theta)</m> as the angle <m>\theta</m> ranges from <m>\alpha</m> to <m>\beta</m> is given by
          <me>\int_{\theta=\alpha}^{\theta=\beta} \frac{r^2}{2}d\theta</me>.

      </p>
        </fact>
    
    
        <figure>
                <caption>Finding the polar area differential</caption>
                    <image xml:id="polarAreaDifferential" width="100%">
